Author: Legana Fingerhut
Maintainer: Legana Fingerhut <legana.fingerhut@my.jcu.edu.au>
Description: A toolkit to predict antimicrobial peptides from protein sequences.
    It incorporates a support vector machine model trained on publicly available antimicrobial peptide data using calculated physico-chemical 
    and compositional sequence properties described in Meher et al. (2017) <doi:10.1038/srep42362> to produce a probability of the protein to be an antimicrobial peptide.
    This is useful as it allows for fast protein prediction on large datasets to potentially discover novel antimicrobial peptides
    on a genome-wide scale
